Salgado Says EFSF Should Seek to ‘Amplify’ Capacity of Its Fund

-- B y   A n a b e l a   R e i s
-- 
2011-10-03T15:09:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/salgado-says-efsf-should-seek-to-amplify-capacity-of-its-fund.html
Spanish Finance Minister  Elena
Salgado  said that the European Financial Stability Facility
needs more capacity without necessarily requiring a
“quantitative amplification.”  Speaking to reporters in Luxembourg, Salgado said that 440
billion euros “well used, can go a long way.” On  Greece , she
said that ministers need to await the Troika report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anabela Reis in Lisbon at 
